        <div id="dsq-comment-header-102" class="dsq-comment-header">
            <cite id="dsq-cite-102">
                <span id="dsq-author-user-102">Anonymous</span>
            </cite>
        </div>
        <div id="dsq-comment-body-102" class="dsq-comment-body">
            <div id="dsq-comment-message-102" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>The invisible posts you&#8217;re referring to are referred to as &#8220;ghost&#8221; posts. Ghosting is actually automated, and has nothing to do with whether or not you annoy CL.. A post gets ghosted when it gets flagged too often over a certain period of time. I don&#8217;t know that CL has publicly admitted to the specific numbers of posts or time periods that they use to determine whether a post gets ghosted, but the process is automated and has nothing to do with them punishing you for reposting &#8211; they&#8217;re punishing you for reposting something that gets flagged down each time it goes up. Now, like I said in the article, flagging is broken, and as such, so is ghosting, but it&#8217;s important to understand how it all works. </p>
</div>
        </div>

